Sentencas: Fuel cells are a promising source of clean energy.
Titulo: Numerical Simulation of Processes in an Electrochemical Cell Using COMSOL Multiphysics

Sentencas: To find optimal parameters for their operation, modeling is necessary, which is quite difficult to implement taking into account all the significant effects occurring in them.
Titulo: Numerical Simulation of Processes in an Electrochemical Cell Using COMSOL Multiphysics

Sentencas: We aim to develop a previously unrealized model in COMSOL Multiphysics that, on one hand, will consider the influence of electrochemical heating and non-isothermal fluid flow on the temperature field and reaction rates, and on the other hand, will demonstrate the operating mode of the Solid Oxide Fuel Cell (SOFC) on carbonaceous fuel.
Titulo: Numerical Simulation of Processes in an Electrochemical Cell Using COMSOL Multiphysics

Sentencas: This model incorporates a range of physical phenomena, including electron and ion transport, gas species diffusion, electrochemical reactions, and heat transfer, to simulate the performance of the SOFC.
Titulo: Numerical Simulation of Processes in an Electrochemical Cell Using COMSOL Multiphysics

Sentencas: The findings provide a detailed view of reactant concentration, temperature, and current distribution, enabling the calculation of power output.
Titulo: Numerical Simulation of Processes in an Electrochemical Cell Using COMSOL Multiphysics

Sentencas: The developed model was compared with a 1-kW industrial prototype operating on hydrogen and showed good agreement in the volt-ampere characteristic with a deviation not exceeding 5% for the majority of the operating range.
Titulo: Numerical Simulation of Processes in an Electrochemical Cell Using COMSOL Multiphysics

Sentencas: The fuel cell exhibits enhanced performance on hydrogen, generating 1340 W/m2 with a current density of 0.25 A/cm2.
Titulo: Numerical Simulation of Processes in an Electrochemical Cell Using COMSOL Multiphysics

Sentencas: When fueled by methane, it produces 1200 W/m2 at the same current density.
Titulo: Numerical Simulation of Processes in an Electrochemical Cell Using COMSOL Multiphysics

Sentencas: Using synthesis gas, it reaches its peak power of 1340 W/m2 at a current density of 0.3 A/cm2.
